---
import LocationLayout from '../../../layouts/LocationLayout.astro';
import locations from '../../../data/locations.json';
import pricing from '../../../data/pricing.json';

const loc = locations.locations[0];
const p = pricing.services.hullInspection;
---
<LocationLayout
  title="Hull Inspection in Brixham"
  description="Underwater visual hull inspection at Brixham Marina. HD video condition report reveals fouling, antifoul wear, and intake blockages. From £10/metre."
  locationName={loc.name} locationSlug={loc.slug} marina={loc.marina} tagline="Visual Hull Inspection at Brixham Marina"
  berths={loc.berths} maxVesselLength={loc.maxVesselLength} access={loc.access}
  foulingFactors={loc.foulingFactors} contentAngle={loc.contentAngle}
  heroImage="/images/locations/brixham-harbour.png"
  breadcrumbService="Hull Inspection" breadcrumbServiceSlug="hull-inspection"
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">
        <div class="content-main">
          <h2>What's Really Happening Below Your Waterline in Brixham?</h2>
          <p>Brixham's harbour doesn't give much away from the surface. You might notice a green waterline developing in summer, or feel the boat sluggish on the throttle — but the full picture of what's happening below the waterline is invisible without looking. And looking traditionally meant either expensive diver time or a crane lift that costs hundreds before anyone's even picked up a scraper.</p>
          <p>Our visual hull inspection solves this with a fraction of the cost and disruption. The Keelcrab Pro's onboard HD camera system scans your entire hull below the waterline, transmitting live video to our operator's screen. We document the condition of your antifouling paint, the extent and type of fouling growth, the state of through-hull fittings and water intakes, and any areas of damage or concern — all captured in timestamped high-definition footage.</p>

          <h3>When Brixham Boat Owners Should Consider an Inspection</h3>
          <p>The most common trigger for an inspection in Brixham is the pre-season check. After a winter in the harbour, owners want to know whether their antifouling has held up, whether fouling has established, and whether the hull needs a clean before the sailing season begins. An inspection in March or early April gives you the information you need to plan — and costs a fraction of a speculative lift-out.</p>
          <p>Pre-purchase inspections are the second most popular reason. If you're considering buying a boat currently berthed in Brixham, a visual hull inspection gives you an honest look at the underwater condition before you commit. It won't replace a full marine survey — we're clear about that — but it reveals things that even a surveyor might not see without commissioning a separate dive inspection.</p>
          <p>Post-grounding checks are the third scenario. If your boat has touched bottom in the harbour approaches or on the way to the Dart, a quick inspection within a day or two gives you peace of mind that no structural damage occurred. Our video evidence is timestamped and can be shared with your insurer.</p>

          <h3>What You Receive</h3>
          <p>Every Brixham inspection produces a visual condition report delivered as a PDF document with accompanying HD video footage. The report includes our observations on antifouling condition, fouling coverage and type, intake and through-hull fitting status, and any areas we'd recommend monitoring. Video clips are shared digitally for your records.</p>

          <div class="disclaimer-box">
            <p><strong>⚠️ Important:</strong> Our inspection is a visual condition report delivered by robotic technology. It is not a qualified marine survey and does not replace the opinion of a certified marine surveyor. We do not provide structural assessments, osmosis testing, or MCA compliance surveys.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="content-sidebar">
          <div class="price-box">
            <span class="price-box__label">Hull Inspection</span>
            <span class="price-box__amount">£{p.pricePerMetre}</span>
            <span class="price-box__unit">per metre</span>
            <span class="price-box__min">Min: £{p.minimumCharge}</span>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn--primary" style="width:100%;margin-top:var(--space-md)">Book an Inspection</a>
          </div>
          <div class="sidebar-info">
            <h4>Common Brixham Inspection Findings</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Heavy barnacle growth near waterline</li>
              <li>Antifouling erosion from harbour sediment</li>
              <li>Blocked water intakes from organic debris</li>
              <li>Silt deposits in hull recesses and keel root</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="other-services">
            <h4>Also in Brixham</h4>
            <a href="/locations/brixham/hull-cleaning">Hull Cleaning →</a>
            <a href="/locations/brixham/maintenance-plans">Maintenance Plans →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</LocationLayout>

<style>
  .content-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr; gap: var(--space-3xl); align-items: start; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .content-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .content-main p { color: var(--text-light); margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: 1.8; }
  .content-main h3 { margin-top: var(--space-2xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-md); font-size: 1.25rem; }
  .disclaimer-box { background: rgba(231,76,60,0.08); border: 1px solid rgba(231,76,60,0.2); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: var(--space-lg); margin-top: var(--space-xl); }
  .disclaimer-box p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-light); margin: 0; }
  .price-box { background: var(--surface); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-xl); text-align: center; margin-bottom: var(--space-xl); position: sticky; top: calc(var(--header-height) + var(--space-lg)); }
  .price-box__label { display: block; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); }
  .price-box__amount { display: block; font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 3rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--primary); }
  .price-box__unit { display: block; color: var(--text-light); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .price-box__min { display: block; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.8rem; margin-top: var(--space-xs); }
  .sidebar-info { background: var(--surface); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-xl); }
  .sidebar-info h4 { font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: var(--space-md); }
  .sidebar-info ul { list-style: none; }
  .sidebar-info li { padding: var(--space-xs) 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-light); }
  .sidebar-info li::before { content: '→ '; color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }
  .other-services { background: var(--surface); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-xl); }
  .other-services h4 { font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: var(--space-md); }
  .other-services a { display: block; padding: var(--space-sm) 0; color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; }
</style>
